news.title: USA: Tenants grapple with rent hikes amid overall inflation spike
news.para: The Miami-Fort Lauderdale-West Palm Beach metropolitan area in Florida saw overall median rent soar over 50% in April from a year ago, to $3,045 a month, according to Realtor.com.

news.title: Dalmia Nisus Finance invests Rs 60 crore in two projects of Shriram Properties
news.para: These investments have been made from the Rs 500-crore fund that primarily invests into structured credit and mezzanine investments across the residential space in India.

news.title: New 2BHK housing project planned in Secunderabad Cantonment
news.para: ​​A total of 296 2BHK flats in five blocks on 1.67 acre at a cost of Rs 23 crore are expected. The construction is to be completed in one and half years.

news.title: Gujarat: Tile makers in Morbi face heat of rising gas prices, lose competitiveness
news.para: ​Morbi is home to some 1,000 ceramic tiles and sanitaryware manufacturing units of which at least 5% are shut, suggest estimates by Morbi Ceramics Association (MCA).

news.title: Maharashtra: MIDC updates 90% of its land records over six years
news.para: "Nearly 90% of record-updating work regarding 66,435.87 hectares of land in the possession of the Maharashtra Industrial Development Corporation (MIDC) has been completed," said a senior official of the corporation.

news.title: Rental houses are back in demand in in Mysuru
news.para: This led to a large inventory of vacant houses at Saraswathipuram, Kuvempunagar, Jayanagar, Gokulam, and other important areas where houses were in high demand. Now all the sectors are recovering, business activities are back to normal.

news.title: Delhi government to modernise property registration process
news.para: Revenue Minister Kailash Gahlot on Friday inspected the offices of sub-registrar and the SDM in Preet Vihar and said that modern technologies will be used to make property registration process easier.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP to share data, conduct drone survey to boost property tax collection
news.para: In a first, the BBMP has tied up with BESCOM to share data on residential properties. Recently, during data verification, BBMP officials found that a plot in Koramangala was shown as vacant land and hence the owner was paying a nominal property tax.

news.title: Union housing minister unveils Rajasthan housing board schemes
news.para: Addressing the ceremony, Dhariwal said RHB has been working out of the box on several new schemes and that it has succeeded in winning the common man's trust.

news.title: Gurugram: Mahira Infratech assures delivery, but buyers worry about delay
news.para: Homebuyers of Mahira Homes fear an inordinate delay in getting possession of their flats, with the department of town and country planning (DTCP) and the developer making different claims about the completion of the affordable housing project in Sector 68.

news.title: Bhopal: Realtor sentenced to life for duping 250 people
news.para: A lookout notice was issued for him after he went missing and he was arrested from Indore airport while he was trying to escape abroad. The court also slapped a fine of Rs 20,000 on the accused.

news.title: ED starts process to sell off Nirav Modi's Mumbai homes
news.para: The ED and income-tax authority had earlier recovered around Rs 130 crore after auctioning Modi's luxury, fashion and art items, mostly paintings, vehicles, and watches.

news.title: HDFC Bank leases 2.5 lakh sq ft office space in Mindspace REIT's business park
news.para: The office tower, which is part of Mindspace business park’s first phase, is currently under development and is expected to be completed in the next 3-4 months when the bank will start its fit-out work.

news.title: Adjudicating or appellate authority can't sit in appeal over commercial wisdom of CoC: SC
news.para: The apex court observed that interference would be warranted only when the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) or the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) finds the decision of CoC to be "wholly capricious" and arbitrary.

news.title: Uphaar fire: Ansal brothers tampering with evidence eroded judicial integrity, court told
news.para: ​The prosecution submitted to District Judge Dharmesh Sharma while opposing a plea filed by the Ansal brothers challenging their conviction and the 7-year jail terms by a magisterial court in November last year.
